      <example> <title>Standard MS-LS2-5</title>
        <p>
          Description: Evaluate competing design solutions for maintaining biodiversity and ecosystem services.
        </p>
        <p><em>In-class exercise:</em> Introduce students to the Rio Grande Silvery Minnow (<url href="https://www.wildlife.state.nm.us/download/education/conservation/wildlife-notes/aquatic/Rio-Grande-silvery-minnow.pdf"/>).         
</p>
        <p>Ask students to research and evaluate different designs and strategies for helping the Rio Grande silvery minnow population recover and grow. </p>
        <p>Discuss with students about the impacts of climate change in the Rio Grande (https://nmindepth.com/2016/08/09/rio-grande-river-101/)  on silvery minnow recovery and discuss ideas on how recovery strategies might be adapted to address climate change. </p>
        <p><em>Take home exercise:</em> Ask students to ask family or community member what the word is for the silvery minnow in their Native language and how their Pueblo interacts or used to interact with the silvery minnow.</p>
