        </p>
        <p><em>In-class exercise:</em> Introduce students to aquatic micro-organisms (<url href="https://water-detective.net/articles/the-unseen-life-of-rivers-mysterious-aquatic-microorganisms/"/>). </p>

<p>Discuss with students the importance of aquatic micro-organisms in river ecosystems (<url href="https://kids.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/frym.2018.00004"/>).</p>
        </example>
        
        <example> <title>Standard MS-LS1-2</title>
        <p>
          Description: Develop and use a model to describe the function of a cell as a whole and ways the parts of cells contribute to the function. 
        </p>
        <p><em>In-class exercise:</em> Introduce students to aquatic micro-organisms (<url href="https://water-detective.net/articles/the-unseen-life-of-rivers-mysterious-aquatic-microorganisms/"/>). </p>

<p>Discuss with students the importance of aquatic micro-organisms in river ecosystems (<url href="https://kids.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/frym.2018.00004"/>).</p>
        </example>
        
        <example> <title>Standard MS-LS1-3</title>
        <p>
          Description: Use argument supported by evidence for how the body is a system of interacting subsystems composed of groups of cells. 
        </p>
        <p><em>In-class exercise:</em> Introduce students to aquatic micro-organisms (<url href="https://water-detective.net/articles/the-unseen-life-of-rivers-mysterious-aquatic-microorganisms/"/>). </p>

<p>Discuss with students the importance of aquatic micro-organisms in river ecosystems (<url href="https://kids.frontiersin.org/articles/10.3389/frym.2018.00004"/>).</p>
        </example>
        
        <example> <title>Standard MS-LS1-4</title>
        <p>
          Description: Use argument based on empirical evidence and scientific reasoning to support an explanation for how characteristic animal behaviors and specialized plant structures affect the probability of successful reproduction of animals and plants respectively.
        </p>
            <p><em>Take home and in-class exercise:</em> </p> <p>Introduce students to aspen ecology (https://www.fs.fed.us/wildflowers/beauty/aspen/ecology.shtml). Aspen tend to grow near streams and rivers and also in disturbed areas like burned forest areas.  </p>

<p><em>Questions: </em> What traits of the the aspen allow it to reproduce successfully? What is the role of aspen in cycling matter and energy? What is the word for aspen in your Native language? How is aspen used by your community/tribe/Pueblo? </p>
        </example>
        
        <example> <title>Standard MS-LS1-5</title>
        <p>
          Description: Construct a scientific explanation based on evidence for how environmental and genetic factors influence the growth of organisms.
        </p>
            <p><em>Take home and in-class exercise:</em> </p> <p>Introduce students to aspen ecology (https://www.fs.fed.us/wildflowers/beauty/aspen/ecology.shtml). Aspen tend to grow near streams and rivers and also in disturbed areas like burned forest areas.  </p>

<p><em>Questions: </em> What traits of the the aspen allow it to reproduce successfully? What is the role of aspen in cycling matter and energy? What is the word for aspen in your Native language? How is aspen used by your community/tribe/Pueblo? </p>
        </example>
        
        <example> <title>Standard MS-LS1-6</title>
        <p>
          Description: Construct a scientific explanation based on evidence for the role of photosynthesis in the cycling of matter and flow of energy into and out of organisms.
        </p>
            <p><em>Take home and in-class exercise:</em> </p> <p>Introduce students to aspen ecology (https://www.fs.fed.us/wildflowers/beauty/aspen/ecology.shtml). Aspen tend to grow near streams and rivers and also in disturbed areas like burned forest areas.  </p>

<p><em>Questions: </em> What traits of the the aspen allow it to reproduce successfully? What is the role of aspen in cycling matter and energy? What is the word for aspen in your Native language? How is aspen used by your community/tribe/Pueblo? </p>
